EFUN: intp

SYNTAX:
int intp( arg );
  mixed arg;

DESCRIPTION:
Intp is used to determine whether arg is of type int.

RETURN VALUE:
If 'arg' is of type int it returns 1, and 0 if this is not the case.

SEE ALSO:
stringp
objectp
mappingp
pointerp
floatp

EXAMPLE:
int i;

i =  intp( this_player()->query_level()  );
// i is now 1.
